<SECOND>PM-Obit-Miller,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Book Publisher M. Hughes Miller Dies at Age 76</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BURBANK, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   M. Hughes Miller, who published the
best-selling ``The Joy of Cooking'' while president of Bobbs
Merrill Co. Inc., has died of cancer. He was 76.
   Miller died Tuesday at St. Joseph Medical Center after his
year-long battle with the disease.
   After starting as a reporter for the Philadelphia Public Ledger
in 1929, Miller entered book publishing with Charles E. Merrill Co.
   He was known for creating the Weekly Readers Children's Book
Club in 1953. He also served as a consultant to such companies as
Random House, Grosset &amp; Dunlap and McGraw Hill.
   His presidency of Bobbs Merrill Co. Inc. was marked by
publication of ``The Joy of Cooking.''
   Recently Miller was involved in Dial-a-Children's Story Service.
His wife, actress Mala Powers, narrated the telephone tales.
   Miller also recently published ``The New Lexicon Dictionary of
Basic Words,'' a reference book for children featuring color
illustrations.
   Miller is survived by his wife, two sons and six grandchildren.
   A funeral service will be held Saturday in Hollywood.
