<FIRST>r w AM-Summit-Stamps     12-01 0165</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Summit-Stamps,110</SECOND>
<HEAD>With AM-Summit Rdp Bjt</HEAD>
<HEAD>Bush Has Souvenir Ready for Gorbachev</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush will present Soviet President
Mikhail S. Gorbachev with a souvenir postage stamp sets on the
final day of their summit meeting off Malta, the U.S. Postal
Service announced Friday.
   The Postal Service said Bush would present the Soviet leader on
Sunday with an album containing the U.S. and Soviet space souvenir
sheets of stamps that both nations issued Nov. 24 at the World
Stamp Expo '89 in Washington.
   The ceremony will take place aboard the USS Belknap.
   The U.S. souvenir sheet features four airmail stamps each
depicting possible future forms of postal transportation. The
Soviet sheets depicts past and possible future milestones in space
exploration.
   The Postal Service anouncement also said it is issuing a special
pictorial cancellation with the USS Belknap designation, the flags
of the two nations and the words ``Conference at Sea.''
   The album being presented by Bush will be stamped with the
cancellation.
</TEXT>
