<FIRST>u a AM-WeatherpageWeather     12-01 0189</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Weatherpage Weather,0194</SECOND>
<HEAD>Snow in the West</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Snow fell in New Mexico and Colorado on Friday and was expected
in parts of the Midwest, while heavy rains dampened parts of Texas.
   Four inches of snow was recorded at Angel Fire, N.M., and 3
inches fell overnight at Trinidad, Colo.
   A winter storm watch for locally heavy snow was posted for
Friday night and Saturday over portions of norther Michigan. Lesser
accumulations were expected in the lower parts of the state. A
winter storm watch for locally heavy snow Saturday night and Sunday
was posted for the northern portions of Indiana.
   Midday snow showers were reported in western New York, southern
Pennsylvania and northern Vermont.
   Rain fell in the western portion of the Texas Panhandle,
northwest texas and the south-central part of the state and along
the Gulf Coast. Heavier rainfall included almost a half-inch at
Dalhart, Texas.
   The nation's low Friday morning was 13 degrees below zero at
West Yellowstone, Mont. Temperatures around the country at 3 p.m.
EST ranged from 4 degrees at Saranac Lake, N.Y., to 77 degrees at
Key West, Fla.
</TEXT>
