<FIRST>r f BC-UAW-ChryslerCommittee     12-01 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-UAW-Chrysler Committee,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>UAW Bargaining Committee For Chrysler Talks Set</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   United Auto Workers leaders have tapped 10
rank-and-file union members to join their president and a Chrysler
Corp. vice president on the UAW bargaining committee for next
year's negotiations with the automaker.
   The union's team, named Thursday during a meeting in Louisville,
Ky., will be headed by UAW President Owen Bieber and Vice President
Stan Marshall. Heading the Chrysler team will be company Vice
President Anthony St. John.
   Subcommittees will be formed to talk about specific issues.
   An opening date for the talks has not been set, but it's likely
to be sometime in the summer. The union's contracts with General
Motors Corp., Ford Motor Co. and Chrysler expire at midnight, Sept.
14, 1990.
</TEXT>
