<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market staged a sharp broad-based
rally in brisk afternoon trading today.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials jumped 47.57 points to
2,753.84 at 2 p.m. EST. The blue-chip indicator was 30.50 points
higher at noon.
   Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by nearly 2 to 1 on the
New York Stock Exchange, with 967 issues up, 488 down and 473
unchanged.
   Volume on the floor of the Big Board came to 150.40 million
shares.
   Analysts said the sharp rally took many observers off guard.
   ``I'm as shocked as anybody,'' said Brad Weeks, head of equity
trading for Donaldson, Lufkin &amp; Jenrette. ``I think people are
sitting out there with a lot of cash and have chosen this time to
put their money to work.''
   ``The upside is not a surprise, but 50 points certainly is,''
said Thomas Walsh, head of equity trading for Nikko Securities
International.
   Analysts said computerized program strategies was helping fuel
the rally.
   ``I wouldn't say it's leading the rally but it's a definite
factor,'' Walsh said.
   A combination of positive sentiment also boosted prices,
including this weekend's summit between President Bush and Soviet
leader Mikhail Gorbachev in Malta.
   The market also got help from economic reports that pointed to a
sluggish fourth-quarter economy, reflecting expectations that the
Federal Reserve will cut short-term interest rates to stimulate
growth.
   The government reported today that its chief economic
forecasting gauge, the Index of Leading Economic Indicators, fell
0.4 percent in October, the sixth month of declines or no gain this
year.
   That report was followed by the Purchasing Management
Association's November report showing an unexpected decline in the
group's index to 46.6 percent from 47.6 percent in October. A
reading below 50 percent indicates a contraction in the nation's
manufacturing sector.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks was
up 2.68 to 193.98.
   At the American Stock Exchange, the market value index advanced
1.84 to 375.68.
